                            <comment id="12924902" author="knutanders" created="Tue, 26 Oct 2010 10:13:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that removes the first check for !waitForLock, so that the latch release code isn&apos;t hidden. The second identical check right after latch release will make sure that the exception is still raised.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All the regression tests ran cleanly with the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12926209" author="knutanders" created="Fri, 29 Oct 2010 09:33:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1028639.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12926217" author="knutanders" created="Fri, 29 Oct 2010 10:12:28 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch (#2) that addresses the other issue mentioned in the description. The patch removes the second parameter (forInsert) in lockPositionForWrite() because it is always false in the current code, and because the method is not believed to work for inserts anyhow.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
